President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Troy D. Edgar of California as the Chief Financial Officer for the Department of Homeland Security. Edgar is the President, CEO, and Founder of Global Conductor, Inc. and has previously served as the Mayor of Los Alamitos, California. He has also worked for PricewaterhouseCoopers LLC, the Boeing Corporation, and the McDonnell Douglas Aircraft Company. Edgar is a United States Navy veteran and holds an M.B.A. and a B.S. in Business Administration from the University of Southern California.

Additionally, President Trump intends to appoint Edward W. Felten of New Jersey for an additional six-year term as a Member of the Privacy and Civil Liberties Oversight Board. Furthermore, he announced his intent to appoint Thomas A. Kennedy of Massachusetts and Stephen Schmidt of Virginia as Members of the President's National Security Telecommunications Advisory Committee.